# Without this file, Windows Git (core.autocrlf) and Linux/macOS Git disagree
# on line endings for every text file, which is exactly what surfaced as
# spurious "modified" files after this session's commits (made from a Linux
# environment) were pulled on Windows. Forcing LF here isn't just cosmetic:
# scripts/hooks/pre-commit is a shell script executed via its #!/usr/bin/env
# bash shebang — if autocrlf ever converts it to CRLF, Git Bash fails to run
# it at all ("bad interpreter"), silently disabling the safety net this repo
# just added. LF, unconditionally, for every text file, on every platform.

* text=auto eol=lf

*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
